# Kotlin & Compose

## Stack defaults

- Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, Material 3, Navigation Compose, ViewModel + StateFlow
- Room for app data; bundled SQLite/asset DB for the lexicon
- Prefer coroutines + viewModelScope; no blocking calls on the main thread

## Structure

- Packages: data/ (Room, assets, repos), domain/ (segmenter, memorize, stroke engines), ui/ (screens)
- UI state as immutable data classes; one-shot events via SharedFlow or Channel when needed
- Keep composables focused; put business rules in domain/, not in @Composable

## Compose

- Hoist state; pass events upward rather than reaching into ViewModels from deep children
- Use Modifier parameters; avoid hard-coded sizes unless matching the parchment-tile design
- Preview small pure UI pieces; do not require Room in @Preview
- Phone stacked nav; tablet may use two-pane Reader | Study

## Room / data

- Entities map to plan models (TextWork, Sentence, overrides, PersonalPhrase, stroke stats)
- Migrations when schema changes — do not wipe user overrides or stroke stats casually
- Lexicon lookups are read-heavy; index by surface/traditional form

## Style

- Prefer val, data classes, sealed interfaces for UI/domain events
- Public APIs: brief KDoc when behavior is non-obvious
- No empty catch; log or surface a user-visible failure
- Match existing naming in a file; do not introduce a second style
